the need for immigration,

00:18:55.210 --> 00:18:58.750
and the importance of being
able to bring people here

00:18:58.750 --> 00:19:01.280
from other countries to be
able to work for Google.

00:19:01.280 --> 00:19:04.340
Have you guys talked
about this internally?

00:19:04.340 --> 00:19:05.590
Does this come up in meetings?

00:19:08.170 --> 00:19:10.160
JESSE HAINES: I mean, yes.

00:19:10.160 --> 00:19:13.300
And we can get the
group involved in this.

00:19:13.300 --> 00:19:16.375
Googlers are
opinionated and not shy.

00:19:16.375 --> 00:19:20.270
A lot of the discourse goes
on, I think, face-to-face,

00:19:20.270 --> 00:19:23.200
but also there's a
number of online places

00:19:23.200 --> 00:19:27.730
where Google can discuss
and get into the issues.

00:19:27.730 --> 00:19:31.887
I know that Sundar
has spoken out--

00:19:31.887 --> 00:19:33.220
MARY SKAFIDAS: Very vocal, yeah.

00:19:33.220 --> 00:19:38.500
JESSE HAINES: --on
immigration, and has personally

00:19:38.500 --> 00:19:42.415
committed funds to
support certain issues.

00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:46.785
And maybe there's
folks in the room

00:19:46.785 --> 00:19:47.910
who can speak more to this.

00:19:47.910 --> 00:19:54.730
I also read that Larry
and Sergey, our founders,

00:19:54.730 --> 00:19:55.930
are also immigrants.

00:19:55.930 --> 00:20:00.940
And I came across an
article that was critical,

00:20:00.940 --> 00:20:04.270
actually, of Larry in
particular for being

00:20:04.270 --> 00:20:06.370
quieter on immigration.

00:20:06.370 --> 00:20:13.150
So I think Google demands
a lot of its leadership

00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:15.100
when it comes to these issues.

00:20:15.100 --> 00:20:16.720
MARY SKAFIDAS: But
I think companies

00:20:16.720 --> 00:20:19.930
being vocal about this is going
to be one of the things that's

00:20:19.930 --> 00:20:21.640
going to help turn the tide.

00:20:21.640 --> 00:20:25.557
I mean, John Tish, who
